The paper focuses on developing a crowd-based route recommendation system, which involves human workers in evaluating candidate routes. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) category. Additionally, the paper utilizes optimization techniques and algorithms to generate informative questions and select eligible workers, indicating a potential fit with Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-categories. The system also involves social aspects, such as feedback from workers, which aligns with the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques to find the best route, which suggests a possible fit with the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
